&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a dynamic, highly motivated Personal Assistant to join the Quality Improvement &amp; Governance Team for a 2 year fixed term contract or internal secondment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should be able to demonstrate excellent communication skills, having a professional, friendly and positive attitude. You will be expected to work autonomously helping with a variety of tasks, including minute taking, managing diaries, and planning meetings. You must have excellent organisational skills and be able to prioritise your workload effectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vacancy may be closed early due to high volume of applications.&lt;/p&gt;
